  <section class="profiles-section">
    <h2>Country profiles identified</h2>
    <div class="profiles-grid">

      <div class="profile-card profile-nordic">
        <h3>Nordic restrictive model (DK / SE / NO)</h3>
        <p>Immigrant share 17–21%. Non-Western immigrants show consistently negative fiscal balances (Denmark: −DKK 16bn/yr; Norway: +NOK 4.1M per person from Group 3 countries). Employment and PISA gaps are large and well-documented. Data transparency is Europe's highest. Policy has shifted towards selection since the late 2010s.</p>
        <p class="profile-signal">Signal: Fiscal, employment and education dimensions all document negative net impacts for non-EU immigrants.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="profile-card profile-anglosphere">
        <h3>Anglosphere points-based model (AU / NZ / CA)</h3>
        <p>Immigrant share 23–32%. Australia and New Zealand show PISA reversal — immigrants outperform native-born students. Skilled migrants produce positive fiscal contributions; humanitarian and family streams show mixed results. Per-category breakdown is central to the policy design.</p>
        <p class="profile-signal">Signal: Skills-selection visibly shapes integration outcomes.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="profile-card profile-southeurope">
        <h3>Southern European transition model (IT / ES / PT)</h3>
        <p>Immigrant share 9–14%. Fiscal data are limited, but Banco de España documents a positive GDP contribution. PISA gaps are moderate. Asylum claims are high (Italy is the Mediterranean entry point). Statistical transparency is lower than in Nordic countries.</p>
        <p class="profile-signal">Signal: Labour immigration increasingly filling demographic gaps from very low birth rates.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="profile-card profile-central">
        <h3>Central European emerging model (CZ / AT)</h3>
        <p>Austria: 20.5% immigrant share, asylum claims peaked at Europe's highest per-capita levels in 2022–23. Czechia: 10.4%, with Ukrainian refugees making up 54% of all foreign nationals. Fiscal and PISA data are under construction or unavailable. Integration infrastructure is still developing.</p>
        <p class="profile-signal">Signal: Rapid inflows after decades of low immigration — data systems lagging behind reality.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="methodology-note">
    <h2>Methodological note</h2>
    <p>Each cell is a summary of data found in the country pages and involves simplification. Measurement methods, reference years and definitions of "immigrant" vary across countries. Always consult individual country pages for precise figures, sources and methodological caveats. A grey cell means "no publicly available primary source confirmed" — not "no impact exists".</p>
  </section>
</main>

<style>
.matrix-section { margin: 2rem 0; }

.legend {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 1rem 2rem;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  font-size: 0.85rem;
}

.legend-item {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.4rem;
}

.dot {
  display: inline-block;
  width: 14px;
  height: 14px;
  border-radius: 3px;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.dot.green  { background: #2dd4bf; }
.dot.red    { background: #e8636b; }
.dot.yellow { background: #f0b429; }
.dot.gray   { background: #7c87a3; }

.table-wrapper {
  overflow-x: auto;
  -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

.matrix-table {
  width: 100%;
  border-collapse: collapse;
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  min-width: 900px;
}

.matrix-table th {
  background: var(--color-surface-raised, #1e2535);
  padding: 0.4rem 0.25rem;
  text-align: center;
  font-weight: 600;
  white-space: nowrap;
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border, #2a3348);
  font-size: 0.68rem;
}

.matrix-table th img {
  display: block;
  margin: 0 auto 2px;
  width: 20px;
  height: auto;
}

.matrix-table td {
  padding: 0.3rem 0.4rem;
  text-align: center;
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border, #2a3348);
  vertical-align: middle;
  line-height: 1.3;
}

.theme-col {
  width: 110px;
  min-width: 110px;
  text-align: left !important;
}

.theme-label {
  text-align: left;
  font-size: 0.73rem;
  font-weight: 500;
  padding: 0.4rem 0.5rem;
  white-space: nowrap;
}

.theme-label a {
  color: inherit;
  text-decoration: none;
}

.theme-label a:hover {
  text-decoration: underline;
}

.theme-label small {
  display: block;
  font-weight: 400;
  color: var(--color-muted, #7c87a3);
  font-size: 0.63rem;
}

.cell-green  { background: #1a3d38; color: #2dd4bf; }
.cell-red    { background: #3d1a1e; color: #e8636b; }
.cell-yellow { background: #3d320a; color: #f0b429; }
.cell-gray   { background: var(--color-surface, #141927); color: var(--color-muted, #7c87a3); font-size: 0.63rem; }

.matrix-note {
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  color: var(--color-muted, #7c87a3);
  margin-top: 0.75rem;
  line-height: 1.5;
}

.profiles-section {
  margin: 3rem 0;
}

.profiles-section h2 {
  font-size: 1.3rem;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

.profiles-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr));
  gap: 1.25rem;
}

.profile-card {
  padding: 1.25rem;
  border-radius: 8px;
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border, #2a3348);
  background: var(--color-surface-raised, #1e2535);
}

.profile-card h3 {
  font-size: 1rem;
  margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  color: var(--color-accent, #2dd4bf);
}

.profile-card p {
  font-size: 0.82rem;
  line-height: 1.6;
  color: var(--color-text, #e2e8f0);
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}

.profile-signal {
  font-size: 0.76rem !important;
  color: var(--color-muted, #7c87a3) !important;
  border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border, #2a3348);
  padding-top: 0.5rem;
  margin-top: 0.5rem;
}

.methodology-note {
  margin: 2.5rem 0;
  padding: 1.25rem;
  border-radius: 8px;
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border, #2a3348);
  background: var(--color-surface, #141927);
}

.methodology-note h2 {
  font-size: 1rem;
  margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
}

.methodology-note p {
  font-size: 0.82rem;
  line-height: 1.6;
  color: var(--color-muted, #7c87a3);
}
</style>

</BaseLayout>
